Preheat the oven to 200C/400F/Gas 6. Grease a small ovenproof dish.Whisk the egg in a bowl, then whisk in the milk.Put the flour in a separate bowl, then slowly whisk in the egg mixture. Whisk in the mustard.Put the sausges and tomatoes into the dish and pour over the batter.Bake in the oven for 15-20 minutes, or until the batter is puffed up and golden-brown.